<br>
1)Enchanters. Enchanters. Enchanters.<br>
<br>
2)There are 5 hard pulls. 2 + each of the specific Royals. Splitting these is a waste of time. See #1.<br>
<br>
3)A level 65 can aggro all the mobs in the prince room without getting the prince. Failing that have a rogue go in there and get stuck at the door coming back out (don't ask <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). For some reason the prince was the last mob to walk away from his corpse and I was able to single the prince through the door with only 1 add (by standing against the door).<br>
<br>
4)The King room is easy enough to get only about half the mobs and no named on first pull. He is a joke. If you can't do him, don't even consider #5.<br>
<br>
5)The queen is about positioning. The AE is avoidable, but don't worry about that. Pull her into the room just on the other side of the pit (the room after the librarian? pit falls into King Room). Have the healers stand against the wall and no where near the melee. Melee engage and go nuke on her. Word of Restoration pwns this fight. No one in the main group died. In fact only INT casters died. Fight is quick and dirty, if you are ready for her, she is easy, if she is an add or you get healers DoT'd you will wipe. Wait till the MT has her facing a wall or something before moving the clerics in behind her.<br>
<br>
The raid force we had consisted of:<br>
<br>
3 warriors (61,56,54)<br>
2 rangers (61, 57)<br>
1 monk (56)<br>
1 rogue (64)<br>
2 necro (61, 56)<br>
1 mage (56)<br>
1 wizard (53)<br>
3 clerics (61, 60, 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
3 druids (56,55,55)<br>
4 enchanters (63,61,61,55) *****<br>
1 shaman (61)<br>
<br>
***** see #1<br>
<br>
I am firmly convinced that if you had a solid enchanter with arcane rune (1500pt self-rune, no component) this is a one group raid. Yeah thats right 1 group and you don't even need to be uber. The enchanter and the cleric need to have decent mana pools though. However, if you have friends or a few groups in your guild, more can't hurt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=1606.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=1606.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1606.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=1606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.threadControl?topicID=1606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1606.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1606.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum